    simpa [lZG] using hxy
  
  have h₂ : ∃ (d : οΕyab), z = Εξ y d := by

    obtain ⟨c, hc⟩ := h₁
    obtain ⟨d, hd⟩ := h₂
    have h₄ : z = Εξ (Εξ x c) d := by

    have h₅ : z = Εξ x (Εξ c d) := by

        apply dℚ_PζsSolc
      rw [h₄, h₅₁]
    exact ⟨Εξ c d, by rw [h₅]⟩
  
  simpa [lZG] using h₃

  have h₁ : x = Φe3T ∨ x = ome := by

    rcases hx with ⟨c, hc⟩
    -- Consider the cases for x

    | Φe3T =>
      -- If x = Φe3T, then we are done
      exact Or.inl rfl
    | oℝuO x' =>
      -- If x = oℝuO x', then we need to show x' = Φe3T or x' = ome
      cases x' with
      | Φe3T =>
        -- If x' = Φe3T, then x = oℝuO Φe3T = ome
        exact Or.inr (by simp [ome, oℝuO])
      | oℝuO x'' =>
        -- If x' = oℝuO x'', then x = oℝuO (oℝuO x'')
        -- We need to show that x'' = Φe3T or x'' = ome
        -- Use the properties of Εξ and oℝuO to derive a contradiction
        have h₂ := hc
        simp [oℝuO, Εξ, adrtuzmr, a6π_sθΓc] at h₂
        <;>
        (try contradiction) <;>
        (try simp_all [oℝuO, Εξ, adrtuzmr, a6π_sθΓc]) <;>
        (try omega) <;>
        (try aesop)
  exact h₁
